This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a method for adapting segmentation networks to different MRI modalities. It also mentions the use of anatomical information, which is a common feature in medical image analysis. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as stochastic gradient descent, which suggests it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of prior knowledge and constraints could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The mention of MRI modalities suggests it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of penalty functions and optimization techniques could suggest it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
